New Records: Australia's biggest loss by runs in the tournament's history, losing by 134 runs.
Key Match Events: Quinton de Kock scored 109 off 106 balls.
Kagiso Rabada took key wickets including Steve Smith, Josh Inglis, and Marcus Stoinis.
Australia dropped six catches, contributing to their defeat.
A 69-run partnership between Marnus Labuschagne (46) and Mitchell Starc (27) was the only significant resistance from Australia.
Post-Match Reflections: Australia captain Pat Cummins stated, 'Probably not much needs to be said tonight. I think everyone's hurting.'
Former Australia captain Aaron Finch disagreed with the third umpire's decision on Marcus Stoinis's dismissal.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia needs to beat Sri Lanka on Monday to improve their standing in the tournament.
